text.tspan: Share among unvaccinated people who would get a
Share of survey respondents who have not received a COVID-19 vaccine and who agree with the statement: "If a
COVID-19 vaccine were made available to me this week, I would definitely get it."
Data source: Imperial College London YouGov Covid 19 Behaviour Tracker Data Hub – Last updated 23 November 2022
Note: Months containing fewer than 500 survey respondents are excluded. Respondents were presented with a 1 to 5 scale, ranging
from "Strongly agree" (1) to "Strongly disagree" (5). We consider responses of 1 or 2 to be in agreement with the statement.
